=Description=

John Gilmore:

"artist Danja Vasilev’s Netless, which used a series of transmitters placed on buses and taxis to create a parasitic network that used the movement of the city to transmit data. It was slow because it depended on vehicular traffic flows but it worked for transmitting small bits of data. There is talk of doing something similar in the US with WiFi in the near future but that will be most likely be connected to the existing “closed” Internet."
(http://bezdomny.org/?p=492)


